  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, most countries have legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain sectors are typically required to:\n\n1. Conduct customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Implement anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nHowever, the specific details and requirements can vary by jurisdiction. If you need precise legal guidance, I recommend consulting with a qualified legal professional.",
